 Adams: An Emerging Songwriting Genre|last=Falatko|first=Daniel|date=29 March 2018|website=Niche Apparel}}</ref> while \"Murder&nbsp;...\" was inspired by a cat owned by singer Miller's roommate in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.avclub.com/old-97-s-hid-a-missing-cat-saga-in-a-love-song-1798282609|title=Old 97s Hid A Missing Cat Sage in a Love Song|last=Browning|first=Laura|date=4 August 2015|website=AV Club|access-date=18 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by Rhett Miller, Ken Bethea, Murry Hammond and Philip Peeples.\n#\"Jagged\" \u2013 3:27\n#\"Lonely Holiday\" \u2013 4:08\n#\"Oppenheimer\" \u2013 3:28\n#\"Indefinitely\" \u2013 3:41\n#\"What We Talk About\" \u2013 4:10\n#\"Crash on the Barrelhead\"  (vocals by [[Murry Hammond]]) \u2013 2:39\n#\"Murder (Or a Heart Attack)\" \u2013 3:41\n#\"Alone So Far\" \u2013 4:17\n#\"Busted Afternoon\" \u2013 3:11\n#\"19\" \u2013 3:41\n#\"Let the Idiot Speak\" \u2013 3:43\n#\"Valentine\" (vocals by [[Murry Hammond]]) \u2013 3:08\n\n==Personnel==\n;Old 97's\n*Ken Bethea \u2013 guitar\n*Murry Hammond \u2013 bass, vocals\n*[[Rhett Miller]] \u2013 vocals, guitar\n*Philip Peeples \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n;Additional personnel\n*Jon Rauhouse \u2013 steel on \"Jagged\", \"Lonely Holiday\" and \"Alone So Far\"\n*[[Jon Brion]] \u2013 Vox organ on \"Murder (Or a Heart Attack)\"\n*Andrew Williams \u2013 odds and ends\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Old 97's}}\n\n[[Category:Old 97's albums]]\n[[Category:1999 albums]]\n[[Category:Elektra Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "Holiday56", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fight_Songs_(Old_97%27s_album)"}
